    <text type="note" xml:lang="ru" xml:id="letter-09011"> 
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when-custom="1786-02-22">1786 г. 22 февраля.</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p><rs ref="works.xml#deceiv02">Раскрывайте</rs> при самом <persName ref="people.xml#arn01">Арндте</persName>, чтоб не разронять множество заметок, кои все по листам положены для исправления.
                <note type="editorial">
                    Catherine writes about her comedy <title ref="works.xml#deceiv02">"Obolschennii"</title>, which was first presented on <date when-custom="1786-02-02">February 2 1786</date> (  
                    <bibl>
                        <title ref="works.xml#dnevni02">Dnevnik A.V. Khrapovitskago s 18 ianvaria 1782 po 17 sentiabria 1793 goda</title>
                        , <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 4.</biblScope>
                    </bibl>
                    ). <rs ref="works.xml#deceiv02">This comedy</rs> was then given to <persName ref="people.xml#arn01">Christian Gotlieb von Arndt</persName> to translate <rs ref="works.xml#deceiv02">it</rs> into German. According to A.V. Khrapovitskii's diary, the translation was initiated on <date when-custom="1786-02-08">February 8</date>, finished on <date when-custom="1786-02-22">February 22</date>, after which Catherine left 14 corrective notes, and was ordered to publish on <date when-custom="1786-02-23">February 23 1786</date> (
                    <bibl>
                        <title ref="works.xml#dnevni02">Dnevnik A.V. Khrapovitskago s 18 ianvaria 1782 po 17 sentiabria 1793 goda</title>
                        , <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 4.</biblScope>
                    </bibl>
                    ). <persName ref="people.xml#arn01">Arndt</persName> would usually receive 300 rubles for translating one play (
                    <bibl>
                        <title ref="works.xml#filolz01">Filologicheskie zaniatiia Ekateriny II</title>
                        , <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 440.</biblScope>
                    </bibl>
                    ).
                </note></p>
        </body>
